# core-be guardrails (advisory)

These complement the executable hooks (Claude `PreToolUse`, Cursor
`beforeShellExecution`). Cursor cannot block file writes, so treat the
file-level rules below as hard policy.

## Never
- **Secrets** — never write real secrets to source. `.env*` files (except
  `.env.example`) are gitignored; put template keys in `.env.example` and real
  values in the environment. Never paste private keys, `sk_live_…`, AWS `AKIA…`,
  GitHub `ghp_…`, or Slack `xox…` tokens into tracked files.
- **Destructive shell** — no `rm -rf`, no `git push --force` (use
  `--force-with-lease`), avoid `git reset --hard` / `git clean -f` on work you
  did not create; never `mkfs` or `dd if=`.

## Confirm first (protected paths)
- **Migrations** (`migrations/*.sql`) — applied migrations are immutable; add a
  NEW migration instead of editing one. Run `pnpm db:migrate:lint`.
- **Billing ledgers** (`src/domains/billing/**` ledger/invoice/charge) —
  append-only; changes must be additive.

## Architecture
- **Cross-domain imports** — a `*.service.ts` must reach other domains through
  their **service**, never their `*.repository` or `*.schema` (see CLAUDE.md
  dependency rules).

## Environment
- Repo needs **Node >= 24** (`.nvmrc` 24.13.0) and **pnpm >= 11.1.1**. If
  `pnpm install` fails with an engines error, switch Node first. Gates:
  `pnpm validate`, `pnpm ci:local`.
